metadata.name: palimpsest #28
metadata.description:
This project channels my old "cursed collage" work with my intense enthusiasm to work ///as fast as I can/// with digital tools
I like to work with very old, cheap and popular consumer magazines. All the analogical graphic resources that I use are images, photos, papers that friends , lovers and  acquaintances gave me when they learned of my need to understand how popular culture can be a personal oracle

metadata.name: Outside your Window #51
metadata.description:
Never take for granted that we sit in the safety of our homes, behind our windows, sheltered from the elements outside. 

The characteristics of the rain outside the window, and the window itself, will be determined by the mint hash. However, the background color of this piece will constantly change based on the hour of day it is loaded, hence note that the thumbnail will only technically be accurate 1/24 hours out of the day as it represents a static snapshot taken at the time of token rendering.

100% of the primary proceeds will be donated towards flood relief efforts for the devastating December 2021 floods in Malaysia.

Made in p5js
Created December 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: ᴘᴏʟʟᴏᴋ'ꜱ 𝖜𝖊𝖙 ᴅʀᴇᴀᴍ #3
metadata.description:
The painter climbed the stairs to his dilapidated workshop. 
He did not see well where he stepped, it had been a hard day of cirrhosis and smoke in his eyes. 
Right on the bottom rung, he let his foot slip, tripped, and hit his head violently on the floor. 

Then, it began one of his most lucid journeys.

metadata.name: Retroscapes #187
metadata.description:
You are approaching newly discovered planetary ring system, seen by no human before.
Gravity works in strange ways there. Intrigued, you grab your polaroid. 
Snap, and there it is - your grainy Retroscape.

Beauty comes from diversity.

Size of the collection - 222 pieces - is a tribute to my first NFT.

metadata.name: Euphonic #169
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Visa to the stars #485
metadata.description:
Generative space scenes with an illustrative look.

Use the capture functions to export in big after opening it in its own window, the artwork is full of details.

Press SPACE to show/hide the menu

Control the camera and explore the scene with :
- Mouse Left : Rotate
- Mouse Right : Pan
- Mouse Middle : Zoom

I wrote an article about the project, with a technical breakdown of the piece at https://ulucode.com/wp/visa-to-the-stars/


Decent GPU REQUIRED, you can tune the performances with the "Quality" setting in the menu.
Better performances with Chrome.

Keyboard shortcuts:
SPACE : show/hide menu
A : toggle anti-aliasing
C : take a capture of the ccurrently selected resolution
R : reset camera position/orientation
S : display stats
P : pause animation

metadata.name: miniGlyph #11
metadata.description:
In celebration of #tezos4tezos I am releasing this mini version of a more complex work in progress. 

Every 24th mint (ex: 1, 24, 48, 72, etc) will receive a free physical woodcut.
https://alleditions.art/p/miniglyph

This project is designed such that it can export a layered vector SVG that can be used for plotting or cutting out of wood with a laser or paper with a Cricut.

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: Сhemical realities #50
metadata.description:
As the analog image ages, it decays, gradually turning into noise. It is interesting that this noise and aesthetics of decay are readily reproduced by neural networks, which creates symptoms of destruction and chemical realities that never physically existed.

These idyllic landscapes never existed either.

But a very similar image hung on the wall in my parents' country house.

We've added Perlin noise to the work, making fun of these synthetic digital illusions that are so easy to believe.

Artwork is based on PNG layers (with masks), Disco Diffusion, python and p5.js code.

metadata.name: (un)existing #186
metadata.description:
The existing nature grows on the unexisting spirits.

Generative sketch, based on the pen and ink drawings of Po Sheng Chen. Po Sheng Chen is an Architect who has drawn nothing but Architecture for over 25 years. He tried to explore something different from his previous style (Brutalism with Magical Realism), so developed his own Minimalist Architecture process and style. After breaking up all the complicated elements and symbols, he chose a simple and naive way to present “pure volumes in the space (the essential of Architecture)”: the Use of different densities of vertical lines to create different faces of volumes, with the addition of horizontal lines to create shadows on the volumes. Shadow determined the form of volumes, then they became a clear composition in the space, Eliminating chaos. These lines seem like spirits to Po Sheng Chen, because they represent the soul of Architecture, but they do not have a specific form or meaning...they are between existing and unexisting! Tezumie is a creative generative artist. He saw the latest experimental drawings of Po Sheng Chen, and after reaching out, the collab was formed with the goal of creating a digital representation of the original concept surrounded by a natural and overgrown environment. The combination of nature and architecture.

Made in p5js.
